"Scottish (western Scotland): habitational name from Buchanan in Stirlingshire, perhaps named with Gaelic <i>buth chanain</i> ‘house of the canon’.","Irish: adopted for <b>Ó Buadhachanáin</b>, see   Bohannon  .","History: This is the name of a Scottish clan associated with lands on the eastern shores of Loch Lomond and in the Lennox. — The name Buchanan was brought independently to North America from Scotland by several different bearers in the 17th and 18th centuries. George Buchanan came to MD in 1698. — James Buchanan (1791–1868), 15th President of the US (1857–61), was born near Mercersburg, PA, the son of a successful land speculator and store keeper, who had emigrated to PA from Scotland in 1783."],"variants":[{"name":"Buchannon","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Buchanan  . This form of the surname is rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Buckhanan","meanings":["Altered form of Scottish   Buchanan  ."]},{"name":"Bohannon","meanings":["Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Buadhachanáin</b>, a double diminutive of <i>buadhach</i> ‘victorious’. The surname is also Anglicized   Bohan  ."]},{"name":"Buchanon","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Buchanan  ."]},{"name":"Buchannan","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Buchanan  ."]}]},{"name":"Adela","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Adele  , especially popular in the late 19th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Adella","meanings":["form of   Adele  , especially popular in the late 19th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Adela Buchanan was born about 1215, in East Lothian, Scotland, United Kingdom. She married Donald Le Nae Peer in Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"abt. 1215–":"umbes 1215–Surnud","1210–1304":"1210–1304","1280–1329":"1280–1329","1255–1346":"1255–1346","1215–Female":"1215–Surnud","1304":"1304","1215":"1215","1346":"1346","abt. 1215":"umbes 1215","1255":"1255","1210":"1210","befor